    "In instruction tuning, however, the continuations are natural human-like responses to an input query rather than a simple continuation of what has already been said.",
    "Fine tuningSince instruction-tuned LLMs have already been fine-tuned to follow instructions and respond to user queries, it is natural to wonder whether further fine-tuning can train the LLM to also provide course-specific answers to queries.",
    "There are, however, several issues to the finetuning approach that limit its effectiveness for coursealignment.First, fine-tuning generally requires a significant amount of data, with input/output pairs numbering in the thousands [7], many of which must be hand-labeled.",
    "This is cost-prohibitive and requires the labelers to have a deep understanding of the types of queries that students will make, which is usually not available until a large dataset of actual student queries has been collected.",
    "This circular dependency alone limits the effectiveness of fine-tuning."
